vestigating...',100,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDk0YzgyYmQtZWYwYS00NjBjLWI0Y2MtOTUxZDRhNWU1ZDZhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjU5OTg5NDc@.jpg',1949,'Comedy, Musical, Romance','English','David Miller','Edmund Beloin, Richard L. Breen','Robert L. Welch','Robert Emmett Dolan','Lionel Lindon','Arthur P. Schmidt'),('Jolson Sings Again',6.6,'In this sequel to The Jolson Story, we pick up the singer\'s career just as he has returned to the stage after a premature retirement. But his wife has left him and the appeal of the spotlight isn\'t what it used to be. This time Jolson trades in the stage for life in the fast lane: women, horses, travel. It takes the death of Moma Yoelson and World War II to bring Jolson back to earth - and to the stage. Once again teamed with manager Steve Martin, Jolson travels the world entertaining troops everywhere from Alaska to Africa. When he finally collapses from exhaustion it takes young, pretty nurse Ellen Clark to show him there\'s more to life than \"just rushing around\".',96,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOWY2YTExNDktMTA5Zi00ZTY5LWIyNGItYTBiMTg3ZjBlMTkyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjIyNjE2NA@@.jpg',1949,'Biography, Music','English','Henry Levin','Sidney Buchman','Sidney Buchman','George Duning','William E. Snyder','William A. Lyon'),('A Connecticut Yankee in King Arthur\'s Court',6.5,'A bump on the head sends Hank Martin, 1912 mechanic, to Arthurian Britain, 528 A.D., where he is befriended by Sir Sagramore le Desirous and gains power by judicious use of technology. He and Alisande, the King\'s niece, fall in love at first sight, which draws unwelcome attention from her fiancée Sir Lancelot; but worse trouble befalls when Hank meddles in the kingdom\'s politics.',106,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQ2MzM0NzE4N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwODIyNDcxMQ@@.jpg',1949,'Comedy, Family, Fantasy, Musical','English','Tay Garnett','Edmund Beloin, Mark Twain','Robert Fellows','Victor Young','Ray Rennahan','Archie Marshek'),('The Emperor Waltz',6.1,'T