re temporarily causes him to feel and act like a teenager, including correcting his vision. When his wife gets a dose that is even larger, she regresses even further into her childhood. When an old boyfriend meets her in this state, he believes that her never wanting to see him again means a divorce and a chance for him.',97,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTBjYTI2MmQtZDFjYS00ZDVjLWFmZDItNzIzMWRiYTk3YzQ3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc1NTYyMjg@.jpg',1952,'Comedy, Sci-Fi','English','Howard Hawks','Ben Hecht, Charles Lederer, I.A.L. Diamond, Harry Segall, Howard Hawks','Sol C. Siegel','Leigh Harline','Milton R. Krasner','William B. Murphy'),('Room for One More',7.1,'Anne and \"Poppy\" Rose are the average American family, with three quirky kids. Anne has a good heart and gives lost cats and dogs a home - and one day also the orphan Jane, a problem child who already tried to kill herself once. At first Poppy is worried and wants to get rid of her, but with love and patience they finally manage to integrate her into the family. Just then Anne invites another orphan, the aggressive handicapped Jimmy-John, to their summer vacation.',98,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOWFiZDBmZTAtZmRlZi00ZmI3LTk3ZjYtNTkyMzdiOGU1YWM3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTY5Nzc4MDY@.jpg',1952,'Comedy, Family','English, French','Norman Taurog','Jack Rose, Melville Shavelson, Anna Perrot Rose','Henry Blanke','Max Steiner','Robert Burks','Alan Crosland Jr.'),('People Will Talk',7.4,'Successful and well-liked, Dr. Noah Praetorius becomes the victim of a witch hunt at the hands of Professor Elwell, who disdains Praetorius\'s unorthodox medical views and also questions his relationship with the mysterious, ever-present Mr. Shunderson. Fuel is added to the fire when Praetorius befriends young Deborah Higgins, who has become suicidal at the prospect of having a baby by her ex boyfriend, a military reservist who was called up for service in the Korean War and killed in action.',110,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images