rious rooms. Mabel ends up in one, hiding under the bed of an elderly husband. Enter the jealous wife and Mabel\'s lover.',17,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODBjMzVjNjAtYmVmOS00MGNlLTgyOTEtNzFhYzlkNzNjNDNjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzU3NTk0NjA@.jpg',1914,'Short, Comedy','None, English','Mabel Normand','Charles Chaplin, Henry Lehrman','Mack Sennett',NULL,'Hans F. Koenekamp, Frank D. Williams',NULL),('Kid Auto Races at Venice',5.7,'Charlie, dressed as a tramp for the first time, goes to a baby-cart race in Venice, California. He causes a great deal of trouble and confusion, both on off the track (getting in the way of the cameraman) and on (interfering with the race). He succeeds in irritating both the participants and the public.',11,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjBiNTg3M2EtYTdmOS00MzRjLWEzZTctMDYzNTc1Yjk1ZjFkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDA5Mjg5MjA@.jpg',1914,'Short, Comedy','None, English','Henry Lehrman','Henry Lehrman, Charles Chaplin','Mack Sennett',NULL,'Enrique Juan Vallejo, Frank D. Williams',NULL),('Making a Living',5.5,'An out-of-work swindler takes a job as a reporter. After witnessing a car go over cliff, he grabs a rival reporter\'s camera and races to the newspaper office to enter the photo as his own. His rival is delayed when he gets caught in a woman\'s bedroom by her jealous husband. The swindler follows the distribution of the paper containing his \'scoop\' around town where he is once again chased by the rival reporter. Both end up on the cow-catcher of a streetcar.',11,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWEyZDY4MzQtMzllOS00MDY0LWE5M2YtY2YzOWI3ZWEzZDliXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjY0ODg0MTA@.jpg',1914,'Short, Comedy','None, English','Henry Lehrman','Reed Heustis','Mack Sennett',NULL,'Enrique Juan Vallejo, Frank D. Williams',NULL),('Screen Snapshots 1860: Howdy, Podner',NULL,'This entry of Screen Snapshots travels to Las Vegas, Nevada, and Ralph Staub visits and talks to many Hollywood notables as they arrive at the famed gambling city and vacation at a dude-ranch resort and spa. Included among the resort guests are Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Mr. and Mrs. Richard Hart, Yvonne De Carlo, Clara Bow and her husband, former western-movie star and current Nevada politician, Rex Bell. All of the footage shown was current-1949 footage, so there is no (archive footage) attributes that should be attached to any of the names in this film.',10,NULL,1949,'Short, Sport','English','Ralph Staub','Ralph Staub','Ralph Staub',NULL,NULL,NULL),('Hoopla',6.6,'A hula dancer at a carnival sets out to seduce the son of the show\'s manager.',85,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTM2MDY1NDA2MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwOTQ1NzQ4NA@@.jpg',1933,'Drama','English','Frank Lloyd','Kenyon Nicholson, Bradley King, Joseph Moncure March',NULL,'Louis De Francesco','Ernest Palmer',NULL),('Call Her Savage',7,'Sexy Texas gal storms her way through life, brawling and boozing until her luck runs out, forcing her to learn the errors of her ways.',88,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzE1MjM0MTE1NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDUzOTU0MjE@.jpg',1932,'Drama','English','John Francis Dillon','Edwin J. Burke, Tiffany Thayer','Sam E. Rork','Peter Brunelli, Arthur Lange','Lee Garmes','Harold D. Schuster'),('Kick In',7,'Ex-con Chick Hewes (Regis Toomey) tries to go straight with the help of wife Molly (Clara Bow), but circumstances force the couple into involvement in a serious crime.',75,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzcxZTVjNDYtZGYzZS00ZGQzLTlmNGYtODQ4MmQxNzFiZDEyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc0MzMzNjA@.jpg',1931,'Action, Crime, Drama, Romance','English','Richard Wallace','Willard Mack, Bartlett Cormack',NULL,NULL,'Victor Milner',NULL),('No Limit',6.6,'A terminally ill French secret service agent is hired by Hydra, a mysterious black ops organization set up by the government, to fight crime by any means necessary and receive experimental treatment in return. Also, his daughter hates him.',52,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDRlZTU2ZWQtNzdjNS00ODg1LWFlNWItNzNmYWI0MmI3ZD