ving a girl in every port, all of the sailors in the Pacific Fleet appear to have the same girl when in their home-port of San Diego; Miss Ruby Nolan, a counter-girl in a San Diego drugstore. She, in turn, is interested only in the stiff-as-a-board gunners-mate \"Bull\'s-Eye\" McCoy, who is not interested in her. She sets about to change his mind.',71,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE5NmZhNDEtNTJjYS00NzZkLTg1M2UtZDVkNDAwMzRkMDhmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjUxODE0MDY@.jpg',1930,'Action, Comedy, Romance','English','Frank Tuttle','Keene Thompson, Doris Anderson, Herman J. Mankiewicz',NULL,'Howard Jackson','Victor Milner','Doris Drought'),('Paramount on Parade',5.8,'A musical revue that basically has Paramount stars and contract-players doing things some had never done on screen, and wouldn\'t again; such as Ruth Chatteron , in a French-café setting singing \"My Marine\" (written by Richard A. Whiting and Raymond B. Eagan) to a group of U. S. Marines, including Stuart Eriwn, Stanley Smith and Frederic March; Buddy Rogers doing a song-duet with Lillian Roth called \"Any Time\'s the Time to Fall in Love\" (written by Elise Jans and Jack King), on a cuckoo-clock set; and Clara Bow singing and dancing in the \"True To The Navy Now\" number to a group of sailors.',102,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzcxZmFlMTMtMmRhMS00ZjZhLWE4MmItZTYwOTljMTAzODY3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTcyODY2NDQ@.jpg',1930,'Comedy, Music','English, Spanish, French','Dorothy Arzner, Otto Brower, Edmund Goulding, Victor Heerman, Edwin H. Knopf, Rowland V. Lee, Ernst Lubitsch, Lothar Mendes, Victor Schertzinger, A. Edward Sutherland, Frank Tuttle, Dorothy Arzner, Otto Brower, Edmund Goulding, Victor Heerman, Edwin H. Knopf, Rowland V. Lee, Ernst Lubitsch, Victor Schertzinger, A. Edward Sutherland, Frank Tuttle','Josep Carner Ribalta, Joseph L. Mankiewicz','Elsie Janis, Albert A. Kaufman, B.P. Schulberg','Howard Jackson','Harry Fischbeck, Victor Milner','Merrill G. White'),('The Saturday Night Kid',5.9,'Mayme, a salesgirl in Ginsberg\'s department store, is in love with Bill, another clerk; but when he is promoted to floorwalker and Mayme\'s sister, Janie, is made treasurer of the benefit pageant, Mayme loses Bill to her sister. Janie, however, has been losing racing bets placed with Lem Woodruff, proprietor of the boardinghouse where she and Mayme live; and to make up her losses, she places the pageant money on a winning horse, but inadvertently the bet is placed on another horse. She confesses her predicament to Mayme, who wins back the money by shooting craps with Lem. Janie blames her sister for the loss until Mayme shows up with the money and vents her righteous wrath on her hypocritical sister. Bill returns to Mayme, and Janie finds happiness with Jim, a fellow boarder.',63,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzc4MDQ1OWItM2Y2NS00ODA1LThjNjQtYzBiODUwYTgzMDU5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzg1ODEwNQ@@.jpg',1929,'Comedy','English','A. Edward Sutherland','George Abbott, John V.A. Weaver, Lloyd Corrigan, Ethel Doherty, Edward E. Paramore Jr., Joseph L. Mankiewicz',NULL,'John Leipold','Harry Fischbeck','Jane Loring'),('Dangerous Curves',3.6,'A college graduate is offered a deal of a lifetime - deliver a Porsche for a client and join the company of your dreams in return. When the car gets stolen, he and his friend must go to a beauty pageant run by the thief to get it back.',93,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOWQ2MTVlYjMtMWNjZS00OWM1LWI3YmYtMDgwN2Q1MTk3ODUyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjY3MjUzNDk@.jpg',1988,'Comedy','English','David Lewis','Paul Brown, Michael Dugan, Michael Zand','Mark Borde, Lawrence Kasanoff, Kenneth Raich, Ellen Steloff','John D\'Andrea','David Lewis','Bob Bring'),('The Wild Party',5.4,'With the arrival of talking pictures, a silent film comedian (a Fatty Arbuckle-type) throws a lavish party to try and save his failing career. His plan is to release one last, great silent epic. In HD.',95,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWQ5NWUwZDUtZjA1OS00MGU2LWE2Y2EtOG