ers and moves to Metropolis to fight evil. As Superman, he battles the villainous Lex Luthor, while, as novice reporter Clark Kent, he attempts to woo co-worker Lois Lane',143,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzA0YWMwMTUtMTVhNC00NjRkLWE2ZTgtOWEzNjJhYzNiMTlkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc1NTYyMjg@.jpg',1978,'Action, Adventure, Sci-Fi','English','Richard Donner','Jerry Siegel, Joe Shuster, Mario Puzo, Mario Puzo, David Newman, Leslie Newman, Robert Benton, Tom Mankiewicz','Charles Greenlaw, Richard Lester, Alexander Salkind, Ilya Salkind, Pierre Spengler','John Williams','Geoffrey Unsworth','Stuart Baird, Michael Ellis'),('March or Die',6.3,'Foreign Legion Major William Foster (Gene Hackman), an American haunted by his memories of the recently-ended Great War, is assigned to protect a group of archaeologists at their dig. Foster\'s unit includes the charming, thieving rascal Marco Segrain (Terence Hill), who joined the Legion only to avoid prison. After long stretches portraying the boredom and hardship of day-to-day life in the Legion, Foster\'s command occupies a small village where the archaeologists believe they\'ve found a burial site sacred to the Arabs. Arab leader El Krim (Sir Ian Holm) uses this affront to unite the tribes in Jihad, and attacks the tiny Legion garrison at the dig. An epic battle follows, very reminiscent of Zulu (1964). Costumes, firearms, and props are all very authentic-looking, and show great attention to detail.',107,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzFkZDY3YjUtMGFhOS00YTYyLThiOTktN2NhZGRkYTk5ZDI0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjI4MjA5MzA@.jpg',1977,'Adventure, Drama, Romance, War','English','Dick Richards','David Zelag Goodman, Dick Richards, David Zelag Goodman','Jerry Bruckheimer, Lew Grade, Dick Richards, Georges-Patrick Salvy-Guide','Maurice Jarre','John Alcott','Stanford C. Allen, O. Nicholas Brown, John C. Howard'),('A Bridge Too Far',7.4,'The true story of Operation Market Garden, the Allies attempt, in September 1944, to hasten the end of World War II by driving through Belgium and Holland into Germany. The idea was for U.S. airborne divisions to take the towns of Eindhoven and Nijmegen and a British airborne division, reinforced by a Polish airborne brigade, to take the town of Arnhem. They would be reinforced, in due course and in turn, by the British XXX Corps, land-based and driving up from the British lines in the south. The key to the operation was the bridges, as if the Germans held or blew them, the paratroopers could not be relieved. Faulty intelligence, Allied high command hubris, and stubborn German resistance would ensure that Arnhem was a bridge too far.',175,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWRjZmZmYmItYzczOS00NjY4LTk3ODItNGU3ZDQ2ZGJkYmZiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjUzOTY1NTc@.jpg',1977,'Drama, History, War','English, German, Dutch, Polish, Latin','Richard Attenborough','Cornelius Ryan, William Goldman','Joseph E. Levine, Richard P. Levine, John Palmer, Michael Stanley-Evans','John Addison','Geoffrey Unsworth','Antony Gibbs'),('The Domino Principle',5.6,'Tucker is a chronic underachiever and a loser. A Vietnam war veteran who just can\'t seem to keep out of trouble, in the years since his discharge. The only thing he got out of the war was his skill with a rifle. Now, serving a long stretch in prison for murder, he has hit rock-bottom. But one day a man in a three-piece suit visits him in prison, a man he has never seen before, and informs him that he can walk out of prison a free man if he will shoot someone for them, no questions asked.',100,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmM4N2FkZmUtMDMxMy00ZmQ1LTk5OGMtYTkzMmE5ZDExY2RjL2ltYWdlL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjI4MjA5MzA@.jpg',1977,'Drama, Thriller','English','Stanley Kramer','Adam Kennedy, Adam Kennedy','Stanley Kramer, Terry Morse Jr., Martin Starger','Billy Goldenberg','Fred J. Koenekamp, Ernest Laszlo','John F. Burnett'),('Lucky Lady',5.2,'It\'s 1930. Claire (Liza Minnelli), an American living in Tijuana, Mexico, has just buried her 