iations are under way and no one wants to die when they think it will all soon be over. The hill is of no particular strategic military value but all part of showing resolve during the negotiations. Under the impression that the battle has been won, battalion headquarters orders some of the men withdrawn when in fact they are in dire need of reinforcements and supplies. As the Chinese prepare to counterattack and broadcast propaganda over loudspeakers, the men prepare for what may be their last battle.',97,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDcwMDc3ZmItNjMzNi00NTYyLWJjZjktZjU4NWRlZTJlOTRhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDUyOTUyNQ@@.jpg',1959,'Drama, War','English','Lewis Milestone','S.L.A. Marshall, James R. Webb','Sy Bartlett, Gregory Peck','Leonard Rosenman','Sam Leavitt',NULL),('The Big Country',7.9,'Retired, wealthy sea Captain James McKay arrives in the vast expanse of the West to marry fiancée Pat Terrill. McKay is a man whose values and approach to life are a mystery to the ranchers and ranch foreman Steve Leech takes an immediate dislike to him. Pat is spoiled, selfish and controlled by her wealthy father, Major Henry Terrill. The Major is involved in a ruthless land war, over watering rights for cattle, with a rough hewn clan led by Rufus Hannassey. The land in question is owned by Julie Maragon and both Terrill and Hannassey want it.',166,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDAwMTViNWEtNmQ0ZC00NGJmLWJjYWMtMGYxMTYxY2Y0Y2MzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTMxMTY0OTQ@.jpg',1958,'Romance, Western','English, Spanish','William Wyler','James R. Webb, Sy Bartlett, Robert Wilder, Jessamyn West, Robert Wyler, Donald Hamilton','Gregory Peck, Robert Wyler, William Wyler','Jerome Moross','Franz Planer','Robert Belcher, John Faure'),('The Bravados',7,'Jim Douglass (Gregory Peck) has been relentlessly pursuing the four outlaws who murdered his wife, but finds them in jail about to be hanged. While he waits to witness their execution, they escape; and the townspeople enlist Douglas\' aid to recapture them.',98,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjA2M2U5OTMtZGVjNC00N2I5LTg2YjktZWQ3NWIxM2ZlYjFiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc1NTYyMjg@.jpg',1958,'Drama, Western','English, Spanish','Henry King','Philip Yordan, Frank O\'Rourke','Herbert B. Swope Jr.','Lionel Newman, Hugo Friedhofer, Alfred Newman','Leon Shamroy','William Mace'),('Designing Woman',6.7,'When Mike Hagen and Marilla Brown marry after a whirlwind romance on the West Coast, they return to New York to find that they don\'t have much in common. She is a clothing designer who lives in a swanky apartment and whose friends are actors, artists and the like. He is a sportswriter who likes to go boxing matches and horse races. They clearly love each other and make every effort to be flexible. When a mobster, whom Mike has been accusing of fixing sports events, decides to go after him he must pretend to be out of town and mayhem ensues.',118,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDAxZjIwZmUtMjhiYi00NmQ0LWE1YmItNTNiODBkYWZiZjgxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDI2NDg0NQ@@.jpg',1957,'Comedy, Romance','English, Italian','Vincente Minnelli','George Wells, Helen Rose','Roger Edens, Dore Schary, George Wells','André Previn','John Alton','Adrienne Fazan'),('The Man in the Gray Flannel Suit',7.1,'Tom Rath lives in Connecticut and commutes to work every day in Manhattan. He\'s happily married and has a loving wife and three children. Money is a bit tight and when the opportunity arises, he applies for a public relations job with a major television network. During his long commute to work everyday, Tom reminisces about the war. Although 10 years have gone by, he is still haunted by the violence and the men he killed. He also thinks of Maria, an Italian girl with whom he had an affair while stationed in Rome. At his new job, the head of the network Ralph Hopkins takes an immediate liking to him. Tom soon realizes that he will have to choose between becoming a wholly dedicated company man or maintaining a healthy work-life balance. When he learns that Maria gave birth to his son after he left Italy, he decides to let his wife know and ensure that the boy is cared for.',153,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWQwN2MzOTUtZTI0Ni00NjRiLThiOTctYzZkM2QxYThlMjkyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjI4MjA5MzA@.jpg',1956,'Drama, Romance, War','English, Italian, German','Nunnally Johnson','Nunnally Johnson, Sloan Wilson','Darryl F. Zanuck','Bernard Herrmann','Charles G. Clarke','Dorothy Spencer'),('The Purple Plain',6.5,'After losing his bride in a Luftwaffe air raid, bomber pilot Forrester becomes a solitary killing machine, who doesn\'t care whether he dies. The reckless Canadian pilot is both admired and feared by the rest of his squadron in World War II Burma. The squadron physician is assigned to determine the embittered Bill Forrester\'s fitness for duty. To break through the nightmare-haunted man\'s wall of silence, the physician drives Forrester to visit an outpost of English-speaking refugees, which includes an alluring young Burmese woman.',97,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjBjZGYwYTUtMjUzNy00YTAzLTliMmYtMmY5MDc4ZGM2YWYyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjI4MjA5MzA@.jpg',1954,'Adventure, Drama, War, Action','English','Robert Parrish','H.E. Bates, Eric Ambler','John Bryan, Earl St. John','John Veale','Geoffrey Unsworth','Clive Donner'),('Night People',6.5,'Post WWII yarn about a young GI abducted by the Soviets in West Berlin and hauled off to the East. His recovery gets complicated as Colonel Steve Van Dyke (Peck) tries to sort out the usefulness of informants, spies, bureaucrats, and the abductee\'s influential father (Crawford)!',93,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMmZjMDRmMzMtZDU5OS00NzE5LTgwMDQtOWU5ZTRhY2JkNjBkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjA0MzYwMDY@.jpg',1954,'Adventure, Crime, Mystery, Thriller','English, German','Nunnally Johnson','Nunnally Johnson, Jed Harris, Tom Reed, W.R. Burnett','Nunnally Johnson, Gerd Oswald','Cyril J. Mockridge','Charles G. Clarke','Dorothy Spencer'),('Man with a Million',6.8,'An impoverished