f them soon find themselves virtual prisoners when the hotel is taken over by a mob of gangsters led by Johnny Rocco who hole up there to await the passing of a hurricane. Mr. Temple strongly reviles Rocco but due to his infirmities can only confront him verbally. Having become disillusioned by the violence of war, Frank is reluctant to act, but Rocco\'s demeaning treatment of his alcoholic moll, Gaye Dawn, and his complicity in the deaths of the Osceola Brothers and a deputy sheriff start to motivate McCloud to overcome his Hamlet-like inaction.',100,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjU0NjU1NjYzN15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTk0NzE2MjE@.jpg',1948,'Action, Crime, Drama, Film-Noir, Thriller','English, Italian','John Huston','Richard Brooks, John Huston, Maxwell Anderson','Jerry Wald','Max Steiner','Karl Freund','Rudi Fehr'),('The Treasure of the Sierra Madre',8.2,'Fred C. Dobbs and Bob Curtin, both down on their luck in Tampico, Mexico in 1925, meet up with a grizzled prospector named Howard and decide to join with him in search of gold in the wilds of central Mexico. Through enormous difficulties, they eventually succeed in finding gold, but bandits, the elements, and most especially greed threaten to turn their success into disaster.',126,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTJlZWMxYzEtMjlkMS00ODE0LThlM2ItMDI3NGQ2YjhmMzkxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDI2NDg0NQ@@.jpg',1948,'Adventure, Drama, Western','English, Spanish','John Huston','John Huston, B. Traven','Henry Blanke, Jack L. Warner','Max Steiner','Ted D. McCord','Owen Marks'),('Always Together',5.8,'Millionaire Turner, on his deathbed, leaves a million to Jane Barker. A movie addict who believes life is like the movies, marries Donn without telling him about the bequest. Turner gets better and wants his money back, opening conflict for the newlyweds. Throughout the movie Jane imagines her own experiences as if they were taking place in movies with real movie stars in them.',78,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTg