INSERT INTO `movie_all_details` VALUES ('The Open Road',5.5,'Carlton Garrett, son of Hall of Famer Kyle Garrett, plays minor league ball in Corpus Christi. He\'s in a slump when his grandfather calls to say that his mother, in Houston, is refusing a heart operation she needs to prolong her life. She says she won\'t have the operation until Kyle, her ex-husband, comes to see her. So Carlton, with his close friend Lucy, who used to be his girlfriend, goes to Columbus, Ohio, where Kyle is signing autographs. They haven\'t spoken in four years. Will Kyle go to Texas or will he find a way to duck out, as he\'s done for years? In addition to the father and son relationship, what about Lucy, and what about the slump?',91,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTM1NDc5NzYwOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMzc5Mzc3Mg@@.jpg',2009,'Comedy, Drama','English','Michael Meredith','Michael Meredith','Deborah Del Prete, Jordan Foley, Kevin Lee Foxx, Laurie Foxx, Jonathan Gray, Jason Hewitt, Heidi Levitt, Roy Scott MacFarland, Charlie Mason, Michael Meredith, Justin Moore-Lewy, Brigitte Mueller, Gigi Pritzker, David L. Schiff, Suzanne Unrein, Wim Wenders','Christopher Lennertz','Yaron Orbach','Suzy Elmiger'),('The Lonely Island Feat. Justin Timberlake: Motherlover',7.8,'Andy Samberg and Justin Timberlake sing a song for Mother\'s Day during their third collaboration.',3,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDIxNjcyYTMtNDhiZi00MTA0LWI0ZTQtNDY0YmQzYWVjNDgzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjM1ODI1MjE@.jpg',2009,'Short, Comedy, Music','English','Akiva Schaffer',NULL,NULL,'The Lonely Island',NULL,NULL),('T.I. Feat. Justin Timberlake: Dead and Gone',6.7,'Official music video for \"Dead and Gone\" by T.I. featuring Justin Timberlake.',5,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWEwNWQ3OGQtOTIyOS00ZWMwLTgyMWQtYTU4YjdlYmM3NDAwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjgzMzAzMjE@.jpg',2009,'Music','English','Chris Robinson',NULL,NULL,'T.I., Robin Tadross, Justin Timberlake',NULL,NULL),('The Lonely Island: Jizz in My Pants',8,'The Lonely Island\'s massive hit video presents Andy Samberg and Jorma Taccone going through uncomfortable situations with women they find attractive, or even when they\'re in ordinary acts like hearing alarm bells, cellphone ringing or eating a grape. The reason for it: they simply cannot control something happening in their pants.',2,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTE3ZGRmYTEtZDFlOC00ODllLWExNGYtNzcyNzU2YWJiNjU3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzQwMzAwNTI@.jpg',2008,'Comedy, Music','English','Akiva Schaffer',NULL,'Jonathan Lia, Robert Smyth','The Lonely Island','Brian O\'Carroll',NULL),('Rihanna Feat. Justin Timberlake: Rehab',6.5,'Official music video for \"Rehab\" by Rihanna ft. Justin Timberlake.',5,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2VmMzM1MTktNjViNy00OWFmLTliMTQtNTUwOGFkZWFiMzJkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjE0ODc0MDc@.jpg',2008,'Music','English','Anthony Mandler',NULL,NULL,'Hannon Lane, Rihanna, Justin Timberlake, Timbaland',NULL,NULL),('The Love Guru',3.8,'Born in America, but raised in Havemahkeeta in India, with a population of 76, Maurice had always to better Deepak Chopra, and be sexually active, ever since he was 12. His Guru, Tugginmypudha, while approving of Deepak, cautions Maurice and has a chastity belt put around his waist, much to Maurice\'s chagrin. Years later, Maurice has established himself as Guru Pitka in America, but would like to appear in the Oprah Show and be better than Deepak Chopra. When Jane Bullard from the the Toronto Maple Leafs hires him to counsel their star hockey player, Darren Roanoke, to win back his wife, Prudence, from Kings\' star player, Jacques Grande, and also stand up to his dominating mother, Lilian, he agrees to do so - with hilarious results.',87,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTg3OTY1MTQ3MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMDIzMTM3MQ@@.jpg',2008,'Comedy, Romance, Sport','English','Marco Schnabel','Mike Myers, Graham Gordy','Gary Barber, Roger Birnbaum, Josh Bratman, Michael De Luca, Sean Gannet, Graham Gordy, Donald J. Lee Jr., Mike Myers','George S. Clinton','Peter Deming','Lee Haxall, Gregory Perler, Billy Weber'),('Madonna Feat. Justin Timberlake & Timbaland: 4 Minutes',6.8,'The video used soft focus, gentle lighting and airbrushing looks on Madonna. It starts with Timbaland chanting the opening line in front of a giant timer screen that counts down from four minutes. As he sings, a black geometric patterned screen comes from behind and engulfs all of the musical devices present. Madonna and Timberlake enter a house but run away from it after finding the screen there, which starts eating the hands and legs of the inhabitants of the house, thus showing their insides. After a number of shots showing Madonna and Timberlake jumping on and over cars to escape from the screen, they finally move into a supermarket. The screen follows them, consuming the long lines of stalls and the people present there.',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNGUwM2YyZDUtMjMwZS00ZjQ4LTg3NTktODVlODQzOThmNDI2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTk1NTMyNzM@.jpg',2008,'Music, Musical','English','Jonas Euvremer, François Rousselet',NULL,'Svana Gisla, Greg Panteix','DanJa, Madonna, Timbaland, Justin Timberlake','Daniel Landin','Danny Tull'),('Gnarls Barkley: Run',NULL,'Gnarls Barkley performs in the music video \"Run\" from the album \"The Odd Couple\" recorded for the Warner Music Group. The music video features CeeLo Green and Danger Mouse performing on a television dance show. After an introduction by the shows host, CeeLo Green sings while Danger Mouse plays on a turntable. Spinning lighting effects are shown throughout.',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODdjNWQxNWEtNWYwNS00NDBlLWEzYzktNjVkNzQ3NzA0ZmEyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDU1NDIzMzY@.jpg',2008,'Music','English','Richard Farmer, Guy Shelmerdine, Lucas Spaulding',NULL,NULL,'Danger Mouse, CeeLo Green',NULL,NULL),('50 Cent Feat. Justin Timberlake: Ayo Technology',6.4,'50 Cent described the music video to MTV. He said:\"You can see this is not my normal uniform, or get-up, when I\'m in a music video. But it\'s time for me to do something a little different, and this is the perfect time for me to actually change my look. You might see this on the red carpet, but not in an actual music video. The biggest challenges for the video are giving off a natural vibe and not seeming contrived at any moment. For you to actually be comfortable when you\'re actually doing it is a task. At some points you\'ve got a room full of people looking at you at one time, just watching you to see what you\'re going to do. You\'ve got to relax and just do it.\" Timbaland\'s appearance in the music video uses features from the movie Minority Report such as moving computer interfaces with hands. Justin Timberlake\'s appearance is similar to that of his role in his music video \"SexyBack\".',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzAyM2NlZWYtOTMyNi00NzYwLWIzMzMtMzYxZTI2Y2JkNTQxL2ltYWdlL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDE0Mzg3NDY@.jpg',2007,'Music','English','Joseph Kahn',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Christopher Probst',NULL),('Justin Timberlake: LoveStoned/I Think She Knows',6.7,'Official music video for \"LoveStoned/I Think She Knows\" by Justin Timberlake.',5,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTc3MzAxMzctZjJmNy00YmI4LWI0NjItYTVmZDlkNzBjMjUwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjgzMzAzMjE@.jpg',2007,'Music','English',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('Timbaland Feat. Nelly Furtado & Justin Timberlake: Give It to Me',6.5,'It shows Timbaland, Furtado, and Timberlake performing the song at the 2007 Grammy Awards pre-show concert, and is intercut with footage from a studio recording session and from inside Timbaland\'s tour bus.',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzdlZjI4ZTUtMGViMy00ZWJkLWEwZTAtMmQ3MmYwNTUxYWExXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjM0MzAyNTU@.jpg',2007,'Music','English','Paul Coy Allen, Timbaland',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),('Justin Timberlake: What Goes Around... Comes Around',7.5,'Music video for Justin Timberlake\'s song \"What Goes Around... Comes Around\".',10,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMGUxODBjODQ