. She and her boyfriend spend a romantic evening together on a barge where they reflect upon their lives after watching an elderly couple. Then Madonna finds out that she is pregnant and after much hesitation tells her father. They have a few hours of tension between them. Her father eventually accepts the pregnancy, and the final scene is a re-conciliatory embrace between father and daughter.',5,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTc1NjNmYjAtNzMxNS00MGY2LTg5OGItZGY2NDBlZmNkYjYzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDE4OTY5NzI@.jpg',1986,'Music','English','James Foley','Brian Elliot, James Foley, Madonna','David Naylor, Sharon Oreck, Randy Skinner','Brian Elliot, Madonna','Michael Ballhaus',NULL),('Madonna: Live to Tell',7.5,'Madonna performs in the music video \"Live to Tell\" from the album \"True Blue\" recorded for Sire Records and Warner Brothers Records. Madonna sings as she wears a simple flower print dress and stand surrounded by darkness. Video clips from the film At Close Range (1986) play throughout.',5,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzIxMTNkN2EtNzc3My00NjE3LThjMjItZDE3M2MyMDNlMjQwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQ0NzE0MQ@@.jpg',1986,'Music','English','James Foley',NULL,'James Foley, Richard M. Greenberg, David Naylor, Sharon Oreck','Patrick Leonard, Madonna','Juan Ruiz Anchía','Mitchell Sinoway'),('Madonna: Gambler',6.1,'\"Gambler\" is a song by American singer Madonna from the soundtrack album to the 1985 film Vision Quest. The song was written solely by Madonna, while the production was handled by John \"Jellybean\" Benitez at her request. It was released as the second single from the film\'s soundtrack album in September 1985, by Geffen Records. \"Gambler\" was never released in the United States, at the request of Madonna\'s own Sire Records. The music video of the song is an excerpt from the film.',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDA2ZTIzMTktYWFiNy00MTM2LTg0MjAtY2MzNmUyZjVkMDI4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQ0NzE0MQ@@.jpg',1985,'Music','English','Harold Becker',NULL,'Peter Guber, Jon Peters','Madonna','Owen Roizman','Maury Winetrobe'),('Desperately Seeking Susan',6.1,'Housewife Roberta Glass of Fort Lee, New Jersey, is feeling restless in her life, where she has not taken any chances, including in her marriage to home spa retailer Gary Glass, who knows what to expect in her every move, and who is more concerned about his public image with respect to his business than her. If being honest, Gary would consider her uptight. She does have a few diversions, one of her favorite being reading the personal classifieds, most specifically those written by someone named Jim whose ads are always titled \"Desperately Seeking Susan\". Roberta gleans that Jim and Susan are in a relationship of sorts with the ads the only way for him to get in touch with her as she travels around the country. Obsessed with the pair, Roberta decides to go to Battery Park when the latest ad requests Susan meet Jim there. In her sighting from afar, Roberta can see that Susan is a wild, new wavish attired woman, to some extent a polar opposite to Roberta herself. Out of circumstance, Roberta is able to purchase Susan\'s easily identifiable leather jacket from a third party, which in the process leads to Roberta getting amnesia, further resulting in her being able to obtain all of Susan\'s personal possessions, making her believe that she must be who these possessions point to her being. This causes some confusion for Dez, a friend of Jim\'s who has never met Susan, and who Jim, a rock musician, asked to look after Susan in his needed absence out of town for a gig. Dez, a movie projectionist, can\'t help but fall for Roberta who he believes is Susan, while Roberta, in her newfound freedom, falls for Dez in return. What Roberta is unaware of, even before her amnesia, is that a criminal, Wayne Nolan, who has already killed once, is after Susan with regard to some priceless Egyptian earrings Susan has out of circumstance, he only knowing her from that iconic leather jacket. Susan does eventually learn this information about Wayne and thus tries to track down this mysterious woman who has stolen her possessions both to get back her stuff but also warn her about Wayne. Matters will only get more complicated as Gary gets closer to tracking down his missing wife, when Jim comes back into town looking for Susan, and if and when Roberta regains her memory.',104,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTViMzE5MmQtNWUwNC00NWNkLWIxMWUtYzM5NWRmOTk5MDQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTY5Nzc4MDY@.jpg',1985,'Comedy, Drama','English','Susan Seidelman','Leora Barish','Michael Peyser, Sarah Pillsbury, Midge Sanford','Thomas Newman','Edward Lachman','Andrew Mondshein'),('Vision Quest',6.6,'Vision Quest is a coming of age movie in which high school wrestler Louden Swain decides he wants to be something more than an average high school athlete and sets his sights on a prize that many don\'t think he can win - he then sets out to reach his goal alone, without much support from his father or coach. His father rents a room to a young drifter, Carla. Swain falls in love with her and she helps him stay focused and prevents him from losing sight of his goals.',107,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDQzODg0OTQ2MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjEyNjU1MDE@.jpg',1985,'Drama, Romance, Sport','English','Harold Becker','Terry Davis, Darryl Ponicsan','Adam Fields, Peter Guber, Jon Peters, Stan Weston','Tangerine Dream','Owen Roizman','Maury Winetrobe'),('Madonna: Holiday',6.3,'Madonna performs in the music video \"Holiday\" from the album \"Madonna\" recorded for Sire Records and Warner Brothers Records. With two back-up dancers, Madonna sings and dances in a black shirt and black skirt with tights. She dancers in front of a large window containing a man dressed in pajamas.',4,'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjgyZmYyNTctOGI4My00Y2Q0LWE5NmYtMDRiNWNlNzdkODQxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQ0NzE0MQ@@.jpg',1983,'Music','English',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Curtis Hudson, Lisa Stevens',NULL,NULL),('Madonna